George E. BAKER, Appellant/Petitioner(s),
v.
STATE of Florida, Appellee/Respondent(s). CASE NO.: 2D18-1237 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Second District. April 12, 2018

BY ORDER OF THE COURT:

As it appears that the petitioner is represented by counsel in the proceeding in the trial court, the petition for writ of habeas corpus is dismissed. See Logan v. State, 846 So. 2d 472 (Fla. 2003).

VILLANTI, KHOUZAM, and BLACK, JJ., Concur.
